SUMMARY:Youth Clowning with Mick Holsbeke
DESCRIPTION:Unleash your silly side! A playful\, youth-friendly class using improv\, physical comedy\, and clown games to build confidence & creativity\n\n\n\nGet ready to unleash your silly side! This series is all about having fun\, taking creative risks\, and finding the funny in the unexpected. Working as a group to start\, participants will dive head-over-heels into ensemble theater\, improvisation\, physical comedy\, and clown-inspired games\, learning how to turn everyday moments into laugh-out-loud comedy. Whether you’re interested in performing or just want to break out of your comfort zone\, this session is all about embracing play\, thinking on your feet\, and making bold comedic choices. No experience? No problem! Just bring your imagination\, a sense of humor\, and a willingness to get ridiculous. \nClass Details\nDates: 3/2 thru 4/6/26; Six (6) Monday classes \nTime: 4:00 pm to 5:20 pm \nLocation: The Clown Garage at Improv School Eastside Issaquah \n1315 NW Mall Street\, Suite 4 Issaquah\, WA 98027 (next to the Gaslamp Bar & Grill) \nMaximum students: 12 \nAges: 10-15 \nCost: $320 \nPrerequisite: None
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/youth-clowning-with-mick-holsbeke/
LOCATION:Clown Garage at the Improv School Issaquah\, 1315 NW Mall Street\, Suite 4\, Issaquah\, WA\, 98027
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/YOUTH-CLOWNING.jpg
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260302T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260302T190000
DTSTAMP:20260213T160820
CREATED:20260210T211223Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260210T211223Z
UID:10011447-1772472600-1772478000@www.unexpectedproductions.org
SUMMARY:Clown 100: The Foundations of Clown Play with Mick Holsbeke
DESCRIPTION:Step into the playful world of Clown! Explore presence\, vulnerability\, and joyful failure through ensemble play and laughter\n\n\n\nWelcome to the world of clowning! This foundational class invites you to step into the playful\, unpredictable\, and joy-filled realm of Clowning with other folks. Through a series of dynamic exercises in presence\, play\, rhythm\, tension\, emotional expression\, and ensemble play\, participants will explore what makes Clown so hilarious and contagious. Embracing vulnerability and the fine art of making mistakes\, we’ll turn failure into laughter and endless comic gold. Whether you’re new to performance or a seasoned artist\, this series will help you build confidence\, take creative risks\, and refine your Clown instincts. Come ready to play\, surprise yourself\, and find the fun in the unexpected! \nClass Details\nDates: Six (6) Monday classes \nTime: 5:30 pm to 7:00 pm \nLocation: The Clown Garage at Improv School Eastside Issaquah \n1315 NW Mall Street\, Suite 4 Issaquah\, WA 98027 (next to the Gaslamp Bar & Grill) \nMaximum students: 16 \nAges: 18 plus \nCost: $320 \nPrerequisite: None
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/clown-100-the-foundations-of-clown-play-with-mick-holsbeke/
LOCATION:Clown Garage at the Improv School Issaquah\, 1315 NW Mall Street\, Suite 4\, Issaquah\, WA\, 98027
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/100-Clown-Monday.jpg
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR